Let X be the set of all complex numbers with the usual metric. Consider the following subsets of X: 

A = {z ∈ X : |z| = 1}
B = {z ∈ X : |z - 1| ≤ 1}
C = {z ∈ X : |z - 3i| = 1}

Prove that A and C are connected and that B is path-connected, and find the path component of the point 0 in B.
